<HEADLINE>
LUNAR NEW YEAR DIRECT CROSS-STRAIT CHARTER FLIGHTS TO BEGIN FEB.
13
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan. 15 (CNA) 01/15/07  13:15:38 (By Deborah Kuo)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 Lunar New Year direct cross-Taiwan Strait charter flight
services are scheduled to be launched Feb. 13, with carriers from
each side operating a total of 96 flights during the holiday
period, the Ministry of Transportation and Communications (MOTC)
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Six carriers from each side of the Taiwan Strait will operate the
charter flights  between  Taipei/Kaohsiung  in  Taiwan  and
Beijing/Shanghai/Guangzhou/Xiamen in China from Feb. 13-26, MOTC
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The largest number of flights will be on the Taipei-Shanghai
route, with the six Taiwan carriers offering a total of 52
flights from Taipei to Shanghai and two Chinese carriers -- China
Eastern Air and Shanghai Airlines -- offering a total of 36
flights from Shanghai to Taiwan's capital.
</P>
<P>
On the Kaohsiung-Shanghai route, Taiwan's China Airlines (CAL) ,
Mandarin Airlines and UNI Airways will offer a total of eight
flights from the southern Taiwan port city to Shanghai, while
Shanghai Airlines will operate four flights in the opposite
direction, the MOTC officials said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China's Air China and Hanan Airlines will operate a
total of 26 flights from Beijing to Taipei, and Taiwan's CAL, EVA
Airways, Far East Air Transport Corp. and Mandarin Airlines will
operate a total of 12 flights from the Chinese capital to Taipei,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan  citizens  with valid entry permits  issued by the
governments on the two sides are eligible to take any of the
flights, they added.
</P>
<P>
This will mark the fourth year that direct cross-strait charter
flight services will be offered during the Lunar New Year
holiday.
</P>
